  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's origin\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economy\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most countries criminalize deliberate attempts to conceal the source of illegally obtained funds.",
